  "prompt": "How do you find \"coming soon\" projects on Kickstarter and Indiegogo?",
  "response": "To find \"coming soon\" projects on Kickstarter and Indiegogo, you can follow these steps:\n\n### For Kickstarter:\n\n1. **Visit the Website**: Go to [Kickstarter.com](https://www.kickstarter.com).\n\n2. **Explore Categories**: Look for the \"Discover\" tab. You can often find categories or filters here to browse.\n\n3. **Check Upcoming Projects**:\n   - Scroll down or explore sections that may indicate upcoming or \"coming soon\" projects. Kickstarter sometimes features upcoming projects on its main page or within specific categories.\n   - Look for the \u201cComing Soon\u201d tab, which may be available periodically or highlighted for popular categories.\n\n4. **Follow Creators**: If you find creators whose work you like, follow them. They often share information about upcoming projects through their updates or social media channels.\n\n5. **Social Media & Newsletter**: Join Kickstarter\u2019s newsletter or follow them on social media platforms like Twitter, Instagram, or Facebook, where they may promote upcoming projects.\n\n### For Indiegogo:\n\n1. **Visit the Website**: Go to [Indiegogo.com](https://www.indiegogo.com).\n\n2. **Explore the \"Discover\" Section**: Click on the \"Discover\" tab. This section may have links or tabs specifically for \u201cComing Soon\u201d campaigns.\n\n3. **Browse Categories**: Like Kickstarter, Indiegogo has various categories. Sometimes they sort projects that are \"coming soon\" under specific categories.\n\n4. **Follow Creators**: As with Kickstarter, follow your favorite creators. They typically share announcements about their upcoming projects.\n\n5. **Join the Community**: Engage with the community through forums or comments sections. Fellow users often share information about upcoming projects.\n\n6. **Social Media & Newsletter**: Subscribe to Indiegogo\u2019s newsletter or follow them on social media for updates on future projects.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n\n- **Use Search Engines**: You can also try using search engines by typing specific queries like \u201cupcoming Kickstarter projects\u201d or \u201ccoming soon Indiegogo campaigns.\u201d\n- **Third-party Websites and Blogs**: There are blogs and websites dedicated to tracking crowdfunding campaigns; these may also highlight upcoming projects.\n- **Set Alerts**: Some crowdfunding platforms or apps may allow you to set alerts for new projects that match your interests.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to discover exciting new projects before they launch!",
